##The story of the Front Line Healer: No winter is insurmountable

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

//

Three times in water, three times in blood, three times in Lye, and we shall be as pure as can be.

In the course of suffering, Tolstoj describes the arduous journey from revolution to victory. At this time, the front line medical workers in Wuhan also experienced the immersion of water, Lye and even blood, every day in the fight against the plague.
······

Since February 13, the number of new diagnoses and deaths across the country has begun to decline markedly. The dark moment has passed, and the new pneumonia "protracted war" opened the prelude.

The city, once known as "East Chicago, " is suddenly quiet, but tens of thousands more "residents, " more than 40,000 medical staff from across the country have arrived in Wuhan and Hubei.

People call these medical personnel who go to the front line "the retrograde ones" , symbolizing their bravery and bravery in going against the flow of people to the front line. In fact, under the heroic acts that move us to tears, in their anti-epidemic day after day, there are many difficult or touching or tender "everyday" moments in her mind

01

"When you're busy, you don't feel hungry. "
Wuhan Ninth Hospital Nurse Pan Rulan
A month ago, on January 22, the entire Ninth Hospital received notice to become a designated hospital. The nurses who used to work in different departments were scattered and assigned to different floors after assembly. First I worked in the ICU for more than a week. After the ICU was taken over by the Shaanxi Support Team, I was assigned to the fever observation ward.

I've been on the job for 10 years, and I've never thought, why is this so hard? The disease progressed rapidly. The patient was quite well the first two days. After two days, he was out of breath. After another two days, he was gone. The oppressive atmosphere in the hospital abated until mid-february. Both the medical staff, patients, or the people, are increasingly aware of this is a "protracted war. ".

We're still working triple shifts. Day Shift starts at 8:00 and ends at 5:00. No breaks. In order to save protective materials, coupled with repeated wear protective clothing, but also increase the risk of infection. So as long as we get to work, we don't eat, we don't drink, we starve for a day, and then we eat in the afternoon when we get back to the hotel.

Tired of lunch box, we will be in the hotel to make some noodles, with some pickles, "improve" a little life. The pickles were brought home from work. A packet of pickles, divided into four parts with public chopsticks.

When this is over, I'm GONNA have a barbecue, go shopping with my colleagues, and get back to my old life.

02

"contact your family like a message board. "
Zhou Rui, a nurse at Thor Mountain Hospital
(from Longhua Hospital affiliated to Shanghai University of Traditional Chinese Medicine)
I am from Shanghai, from Shanghai University of Traditional Chinese medicine. Too many things, at first thought, also do not remember which day, about February 15 to Wuhan.

When I first got to Thor Mountain, the hospital was still planning. Every day there are from all sides to come to the medical staff, management staff, while working and running-in. We're short-staffed. Everyone's doing multiple jobs. No one stopped there, as long as there is something or a task, a call immediately, such as shelves, closets, beds to carry.
Chinanews.com
After all, Wuhan is not quite the same as home. My colleagues say we're jet-lagged. Communicating with family is like a message board. At one or two in the morning, when I finished work, I would text my family and say, "I'm fine. ". The next morning the family sees it and replies, "okay, you take care of yourself. ". But by then I was back at work and couldn't check my phone.

Even if there is jet lag, even if it is like a message board, I am very good every day on the phone when the heart will be a lot more comfortable, and seems to be a lot closer to home.

03

"support vehicles from all over the country,
All the way to this location."
Nurses Yim Chui and Weng Lingli of Lui Sun Shan Hospital
From Shanghai Fifth People's Hospital
We came from Shanghai, and in response to the government's call, without thinking too much, we came.

Yesterday we came from the road, in fact, there is no one on the way, but a hospital near Thor Mountain, people Mengdi became more. I see a lot of workers, medical staff, and many of our medical colleagues in Shanghai..

Counting the more than 500 people we came with, there are now nearly 1,000 medical staff in Shanghai to support Thor Mountain. Although all do not know, can see protective clothing, the feeling in the heart is not only kind, more is the friendship of fighting shoulder to shoulder.
Chinanews.com
To tell you the truth, in Wuhan, the intensity of the work is quite large, body, hands are constantly because of disinfection or knock the small wounds. The body seems to get used to wearing protective clothing and gloves every day, from pain to numbness.

It's a lie to say you're not afraid, but once you get in here, you see all the support from all over the country coming to this place, and you forget all your fears and fears. Today, waiting for the bus, see the street leaves are green, see the street are out of green shoots. I hope the whole country will be safe in the spring.

04

"I wish that when the Cherry blossoms were blooming in Wuhan,
Life can go back to normal."
Huang Kang, head of Raytheon Integrated Management Department
(from Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital)
On the night of January 20, our ward was put into operation and the intake of patients was completed. At present, there are plenty of materials for living. I am mainly responsible for docking the various places of the caring enterprises, daily contact phone constantly, has received more than 300 caring enterprises donations. We will also donate supplies in the first time all of the distribution to the medical staff.

Many of our medical staff use alcohol to wash their hands during their 10-hour shifts in the wards. Alcohol does a lot of damage to the whole hand. A lot of doctors don't have fingerprints on their hands. Washing, bathing and hand-care products are also hard to buy now. A few days ago hundreds of sparrow antelope sent the first batch of hand cream, shampoo, all of a sudden on the light.

· · · · · ·

On the front lines of the fight against the disease, medical workers who work day and night need to wash their hands 12 times each time they take off their protective clothing. They need to do this every four hours. They need to be exposed to disinfectants, alcohol and other highly corrosive chemicals for a long time, his hands were scarred by corrosion, his face was burned with "plague marks" because of wearing face masks and other protective equipment for a long time, and there was a relative shortage of living materials in nearby hotels, dormitories and temporary reconstructed rest places, the hands and skin of the angels in white were rough and cracked.

And this pair of hands full of scars, although the details, but let the hundred Chiru group can not let go. Baique Ling Group immediately set up a special team to respond to the epidemic, and quickly joined with the China Association for the Prevention and Control of stds and AIDS, the China Foundation for the prevention of stds and aids to get in touch with the front-line hospitals and communicate with them about their needs, set a target of donating 200 million sanitation and care materials.
Bai Que Ling Group responded immediately,
Set a target of donating 200 million sanitation and care materials
As Shanghai Baique Ling Group Marketing Director Fei Qiwen said in an interview: "We want to be more focused so that resources can be used to help the most. When we found that there were many, many white-clad angels from various medical teams across the country going backwards to support Wuhan, we immediately felt that we should do something for these people that we could do. "

"On the road" public service documentary
On February 6, the first truck loaded with 13 tons of living materials was driven from the Baique antelope warehouse in Jiashan, Zhejiang Province, with the shouts and blessings of "refueling Wuhan" and "refueling China" . On the 800-kilometer journey from Zhejiang to Wuhan, the donated materials began to be transported to the Fifth Hospital of Wuhan, the First Hospital of Wuhan, the Wuhan University affiliated Colleague Hospital, the Fourth Hospital of Wuhan... .
Bai Que Ling has already completed five batches of supplies,
The total donation value is 112 million yuan, supporting 82 hospitals in Hubei Province
As of press time, with the donation of materials as a batch of arrival in Wuhan, Wuhan, Wuhan, Wuhan River Shelter Hospital, Xiaogan City Center Hospital, Huanggang City Center Hospital..

Paigelong has already implemented five batches of supplies, with a total donation value of 112 million yuan. It has supported 82 hospitals in Wuhan, Xiaogan, Huanggang, Suizhou and Xiangyang, Hubei, let the front-line medical staff at the end of a hard day's work, with shampoo, body wash, a hot bath, go to bed for tired hands coated with hand cream. Let the hard fight against the plague, more warmth and happiness.

"To tell the truth, I am a little proud, after all, I have contributed a little in my own way, " said the driver of Operation Gazelle, which is the voice of every employee in Pechoin.
Burning News
"The flu is coming, pneumonia is coming, you want your father to be well? ... You should pay more attention in the hospital to guard against infection. I firmly believe that no winter is insurmountable, the virus is rampant at the moment, as well. "

This is an emotional message from a 14-year-old girl, to the parents of doctors on the front lines of the epidemic, who still believe that no winter is insurmountable, that no spring will not come, precisely because of those most worthy of love, still standing in the front line of the fight against the epidemic, for us to stick with and pay.
The doctors and nurses hold on because the life they love.
From all walks of life throughout the country, because the life we love.
Each of us works hard because the life we love.
The coming spring of 2020 will be unforgettable. Because there are too many people in the end is the road to victory, there are too many pairs of clean water washed, blood bath, alkaline water soaked hands, are doing their best to build a life that everyone loves.
